{"title":"HerpesVestibular RamsayHunt v2","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Otorrinolaringología/HerpesVestibular RamsayHunt v2 iPad.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Herpes Vestibular -\\NSindrome de Ramsay Hunt","guid":"Ux9iSNT0sbJ-vPj3KiScQw","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Definicion y Etiologia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"SINDROME DE RAMSAY HUNT (RHS)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"Reactivacion de Varicella-Zoster Virus (VZV) en ganglio geniculado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"Nervio facial (VII) afectado primariamente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"Nervio vestibulococlear (VIII) comprometido en polineuropatia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"1","text":"Distincion con Herpes Zoster Oticus (HZO)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"7","parent":"6","text":"HZO = termino mas amplio (VZV en CAE/pabellon)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"6","text":"RHS = HZO + paralisis facial periferica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"6","text":"Puede ocurrir sin erupcion cutanea → Zoster sine herpete","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"10","parent":"0","text":"Epidemiologia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"11","parent":"10","text":"Incidencia 5/100.000 por ano","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"10","text":"10-20% de todos los casos de paralisis facial periferica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"13","parent":"10","text":"Edad pico 50-60 anos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"10","text":"Mayor riesgo en inmunodeprimidos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"10","text":"Sin diferencia de sexo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"10","text":"Recurrencia: infrecuente (<5%)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"17","parent":"0","text":"Fisiopatologia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"18","parent":"17","text":"Latencia de VZV en ganglios de nervios craneales (geniculate, espiral, de Scarpa)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"17","text":"Reactivacion → inflamacion + edema → compresion en canal fallopiano estrecho","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"17","text":"Degeneracion axonal directa por VZV","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"17","text":"Dano a celulas ciliadas del laberinto membranoso","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"17","text":"Afectacion selectiva de divisiones del VIII","guid":"","children":[{"id":"23","parent":"22","text":"Division coclear (ganglio espiral de Corti)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"24","parent":"23","text":"Hipoacusia neurosensorial → frecuencias agudas predominan","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"23","text":"Evaluacion: audiometria tonal + BERA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"23","text":"Recuperacion auditiva peor que vestibular (~60% hipoacusia residual)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"27","parent":"22","text":"Division vestibular superior (ganglio de Scarpa superior)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"28","parent":"27","text":"Canales H + anterior + utriculo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"27","text":"Evaluacion: vHIT H/A + oVEMP","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"30","parent":"22","text":"Division vestibular inferior (ganglio de Scarpa inferior)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"31","parent":"30","text":"Canal posterior + saculo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"30","text":"Evaluacion: vHIT P + cVEMP","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"33","parent":"22","text":"Forma completa → ambas divisiones vestibulares + coclear","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"34","parent":"17","text":"Diferencia con Neuritis Vestibular (NV)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"35","parent":"34","text":"RHS: dano mas severo, recuperacion mas lenta y peor","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"34","text":"NV: posiblemente HSV-1 (no VZV)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"37","parent":"0","text":"Cuadro Clinico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"38","parent":"37","text":"TRIADA CLASICA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"39","parent":"38","text":"1. Otalgia intensa (precede a erupcion 1-5 dias)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"38","text":"2. Erupcion vesicular","guid":"","children":[{"id":"41","parent":"40","text":"CAE, pabellon auricular (zona de Hunt)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"40","text":"Paladar blando, lengua anterior (CN IX/X)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"40","text":"Puede extenderse a cuello/hombro (C2-C3)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"44","parent":"38","text":"3. Paralisis facial periferica","guid":"","children":[{"id":"45","parent":"44","text":"UNILATERAL, inicio agudo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"44","text":"Grado House-Brackmann (I-VI)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"44","text":"HB VI en ~88% de casos graves","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"48","parent":"37","text":"Componente Vestibulococlear (Polineuropatia)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"49","parent":"48","text":"Vertigo severo + nauseas/vomitos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"48","text":"Hipoacusia neurosensorial unilateral","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"48","text":"Tinnitus ipsilateral","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"48","text":"Nistagmo espontaneo horizontal-torsional","guid":"","children":[{"id":"53","parent":"52","text":"INCLUSO sin vertigo subjetivo (67% en serie Lee 2020)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"52","text":"Nistagmo posicional con cambio de direccion posible","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"55","parent":"48","text":"Desviacion oblicua (skew) puede estar presente → no siempre indica lesion central","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"56","parent":"37","text":"Otras manifestaciones","guid":"","children":[{"id":"57","parent":"56","text":"Disgeusia (N. cuerda del timpano → gusto 2/3 anteriores lengua ipsilateral)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"56","text":"Hiperacusia (paralisis N. estapedio → ausencia reflejo estapedial)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"56","text":"Exposicion corneal → RIESGO QUERATOPATIA (lagoftalmos por paralisis palpebral)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"60","parent":"59","text":"Mecanismo adicional: dano N. petroso mayor → hiposecrecion lagrimal","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"61","parent":"56","text":"Sindrome de Horner (extension simpatica, raro)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"56","text":"Neuropatia de otros pares (V, IX, X, XI, XII) en casos severos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"63","parent":"62","text":"IX/X → vesiculas en paladar blando y faringe","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"64","parent":"62","text":"V → hipoestesia facial ipsilateral","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"65","parent":"0","text":"Diagnostico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"66","parent":"65","text":"CLINICO en primera instancia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"67","parent":"65","text":"Laboratorio","guid":"","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"PCR VZV en hisopado de vesiculas → confirmatoria","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"67","text":"PCR VZV en LCR si sospecha de meningitis/encefalitis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"67","text":"Serologia IgM/IgG VZV (menor utilidad aguda)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"67","text":"Pleocitosis en LCR mononuclear en casos con afectacion SNC","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"72","parent":"65","text":"Examenes vestibulares","guid":"","children":[{"id":"73","parent":"72","text":"EXAMEN CLINICO VIII PAR","guid":"","children":[{"id":"74","parent":"73","text":"Rama coclear","guid":"","children":[{"id":"75","parent":"74","text":"Weber → lateraliza a lado SANO en neurosensorial","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"76","parent":"74","text":"Rinne → positivo (CA>CO) en neurosensorial","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"74","text":"Voz cuchicheada → screening rapido hipoacusia","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"78","parent":"73","text":"Rama vestibular","guid":"","children":[{"id":"79","parent":"78","text":"Nistagmo espontaneo (con/sin fijacion visual - lentes de Frenzel)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"80","parent":"79","text":"Horizontal-torsional → fase rapida a lado SANO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"81","parent":"79","text":"Supresion con fijacion → origen PERIFERICO","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"82","parent":"78","text":"HIT (Head Impulse Test) → sacada correctiva ipsilateral al lado afectado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"83","parent":"78","text":"HINTS (vertigo agudo - diferencia periferico vs central)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"84","parent":"83","text":"HIT+ / Nistagmo fijo unidireccional / Skew- → PERIFERICO (RHS)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"83","text":"HIT- / Nistagmo multidireccional / Skew+ → CENTRAL → RM urgente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"86","parent":"83","text":"VPN >99% para ACV posterior si HINTS periferico (requiere entrenamiento)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"87","parent":"78","text":"Romberg → caida ipsilateral al lado afectado con ojos cerrados","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"78","text":"Fukuda (marcha en estrella) → rotacion hacia lado hipofuncionante","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"89","parent":"72","text":"VNG (Videonistagmografia) → plataforma de registro ocular infrarrojo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"90","parent":"89","text":"Nistagmo espontaneo cuantificado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"89","text":"Pruebas posicionales (Dix-Hallpike, Roll test) → DD con VPPB","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"89","text":"Seguimiento ocular suave y sacadas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"93","parent":"89","text":"Prueba calorica (subcomponente VNG)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"94","parent":"93","text":"Evalua CSH a BAJA frecuencia (~0.003 Hz)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"93","text":"Paresia calorica unilateral >25% (formula Jongkees)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"96","parent":"93","text":"PRESENTE EN TODOS los pacientes con vertigo en RHS (Vanstrum 2024)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"97","parent":"72","text":"vHIT → evalua ALTA frecuencia fisiologica (5-8 Hz)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"98","parent":"97","text":"Ganancia <0.7 o asimetria >0.3 → hipofuncion VOR","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"97","text":"COMPLEMENTARIO a calorica, no reemplaza","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"100","parent":"97","text":"Permite evaluar los 6 canales semicirculares por separado","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"101","parent":"72","text":"oVEMP → division vestibular superior (utriculo)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"72","text":"cVEMP → division vestibular inferior (saculo)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"103","parent":"65","text":"Imagen","guid":"","children":[{"id":"104","parent":"103","text":"RM con gadolinio (protocolo IAC)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"105","parent":"104","text":"Realce nervio facial (59% en serie Vanstrum 2024)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"106","parent":"104","text":"Ausencia de realce vestibulococlear no excluye dano funcional","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"107","parent":"104","text":"Realce laberinto en casos severos","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"108","parent":"103","text":"IMPORTANTE: DWI falso negativo primeras 24h si ACV posterior","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"109","parent":"65","text":"Escala House-Brackmann","guid":"","children":[{"id":"110","parent":"109","text":"I Normal → funcion completa, cierre ocular sin esfuerzo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"111","parent":"109","text":"II Disfuncion leve → debilidad al examen detallado, cierre completo sin esfuerzo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"112","parent":"109","text":"III Disfuncion moderada → diferencia evidente, cierre COMPLETO CON ESFUERZO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"109","text":"IV Disfuncion moderada-severa → movimiento desfigurante, cierre INCOMPLETO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"109","text":"V Disfuncion severa → movimiento minimo perceptible, cierre incompleto","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"115","parent":"109","text":"VI Paralisis total → ausencia de movimiento, sin tono muscular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"116","parent":"109","text":"CORTE CLINICO CRITICO HB III/IV","guid":"","children":[{"id":"117","parent":"116","text":"HB I-III → cierre ocular conservado → cornea protegida","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"116","text":"HB IV-VI → EXPOSICION CORNEAL → cuidado ocular urgente","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"119","parent":"109","text":"Implicancia pronostica en RHS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"120","parent":"119","text":"HB I-III → recuperacion completa ~75%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"119","text":"HB V-VI al inicio → recuperacion completa <50%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"119","text":"HB V-VI + vertigo → factor de mal pronostico combinado","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"123","parent":"0","text":"Diagnostico Diferencial","guid":"","children":[{"id":"124","parent":"123","text":"AUVP / Neuritis Vestibular","guid":"","children":[{"id":"125","parent":"124","text":"SIN paralisis facial NI hipoacusia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"126","parent":"124","text":"HSV-1 postulado (no VZV)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"124","text":"Mejor recuperacion","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"128","parent":"123","text":"Bell's Palsy","guid":"","children":[{"id":"129","parent":"128","text":"Paralisis facial SIN erupcion","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"130","parent":"128","text":"Puede ser Zoster sine herpete → buscar activamente","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"131","parent":"123","text":"Infarto AICA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"132","parent":"131","text":"HINTS + hipoacusia aguda","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"131","text":"DWI/RM urgente","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"134","parent":"123","text":"Colesteatoma con erosion","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"123","text":"Otitis media con complicaciones","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"136","parent":"123","text":"Sindrome de Cogan (bilateral, queratitis)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"137","parent":"123","text":"Sarcoidosis (paralisis facial recurrente)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"138","parent":"0","text":"Pronostico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"139","parent":"138","text":"Peor que Bell's Palsy","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"140","parent":"138","text":"Recuperacion facial completa (HB I-II) en <75% con tratamiento oportuno","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"141","parent":"138","text":"FACTORES DE MAL PRONOSTICO","guid":"","children":[{"id":"142","parent":"141","text":"HB V-VI al inicio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"143","parent":"141","text":"Edad >60 anos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"144","parent":"141","text":"Inicio tardio del tratamiento (>72h)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"141","text":"Presencia de vertigo/hipoacusia (dano VIII)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"146","parent":"141","text":"Diabetes mellitus","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"147","parent":"138","text":"Recuperacion vestibular","guid":"","children":[{"id":"148","parent":"147","text":"SIGNIFICATIVAMENTE PEOR que en Neuritis Vestibular (Martin-Sanz 2017)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"149","parent":"147","text":"Recuperacion de ganancia vHIT mas lenta","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"147","text":"Sacadas compensatorias persisten mas tiempo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"151","parent":"147","text":"Hasta 50-60% con sintomas vestibulares residuales","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"152","parent":"138","text":"Hipoacusia residual en ~60% de casos","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"153","parent":"0","text":"Tratamiento","guid":"","children":[{"id":"154","parent":"153","text":"INICIO PRECOZ (<72 horas del inicio) → determinante de pronostico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"155","parent":"153","text":"Antiviral","guid":"","children":[{"id":"156","parent":"155","text":"ACICLOVIR 800mg vo 5 veces/dia x 7-10 dias","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"155","text":"VALACICLOVIR 1g vo 3 veces/dia x 7 dias (mejor biodisponibilidad)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"155","text":"Inmunodeprimidos → aciclovir iv 10mg/kg c/8h","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"159","parent":"153","text":"Corticosteroide","guid":"","children":[{"id":"160","parent":"159","text":"PREDNISONA 1mg/kg/dia (max 60-80mg) x 5-7 dias + tapering","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"161","parent":"159","text":"Combinacion antiviral + corticoide → evidencia de beneficio sobre monoterapia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"162","parent":"159","text":"Discutir riesgo en DM, HTA, ulcera peptica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"163","parent":"153","text":"Manejo sintomatico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"164","parent":"163","text":"Antiemeticos (metoclopramida, ondansetron)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"165","parent":"163","text":"Benzodiacepinas uso LIMITADO (diazepam, clonazepam) solo fase aguda","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"166","parent":"163","text":"Evitar benzodiazepinas prolongadas → INHIBEN compensacion vestibular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"167","parent":"163","text":"Analgesia: AINE, opioides si otalgia severa","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"168","parent":"153","text":"Cuidado ocular","guid":"","children":[{"id":"169","parent":"168","text":"OBLIGATORIO si HB >=III","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"170","parent":"168","text":"Lagrimas artificiales horaria","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"171","parent":"168","text":"Oclusivo nocturno","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"172","parent":"168","text":"Remision oftalmologia urgente si queratopatia","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"173","parent":"153","text":"Rehabilitacion vestibular","guid":"","children":[{"id":"174","parent":"173","text":"INICIAR precozmente (dias a semanas post-inicio)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"175","parent":"173","text":"Ejercicios de habituacion y adaptacion","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"176","parent":"173","text":"Promueve compensacion central","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"177","parent":"153","text":"Vacuna antivaricela-zoster (SHINGRIX / RZV)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"178","parent":"177","text":"Tipo: subunidad recombinante (glicoproteina E + adyuvante AS01B)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"179","parent":"178","text":"NO es vacuna viva → SEGURA en inmunodeprimidos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"180","parent":"178","text":"Diferencia clave con Zostavax (viva atenuada → CONTRAINDICADA en inmunodep.)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"181","parent":"177","text":"Indicacion por poblacion","guid":"","children":[{"id":"182","parent":"181","text":"Inmunocompetentes → >=50 anos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"181","text":"Inmunodeprimidos → >=18 anos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"184","parent":"183","text":"TCH, neoplasia hematologica, VIH, inmunosupresion cronica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"185","parent":"183","text":"Incluye pacientes en JAK inhibidores, corticoides cronicos","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"186","parent":"177","text":"Esquema","guid":"","children":[{"id":"187","parent":"186","text":"2 dosis IM (deltoides) x 0.5 ml → NO subcutanea","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"186","text":"Intervalo 2-6 meses en inmunocompetentes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"189","parent":"186","text":"Intervalo reducible a 1-2 meses en inmunodeprimidos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"190","parent":"186","text":"Primera dosis idealmente >=14 dias ANTES de iniciar inmunosupresion","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"191","parent":"177","text":"Eficacia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"192","parent":"191","text":"Inmunocompetentes","guid":"","children":[{"id":"193","parent":"192","text":"Eficacia HZ 97.2% en >=50 anos (ZOE-50)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"194","parent":"192","text":"Eficacia HZ 91.3% en >=70 anos (ZOE-70)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"195","parent":"192","text":"Eficacia NPH ~91%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"192","text":"Proteccion sostenida >=10 anos","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"197","parent":"191","text":"Inmunodeprimidos → MENOR eficacia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"198","parent":"197","text":"TCH: ~68-87%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"199","parent":"197","text":"Neoplasia hematologica: ~87%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"197","text":"VIH: ~68%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"201","parent":"197","text":"Iniciar antes de inmunosupresion si posible","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"202","parent":"177","text":"Seguridad","guid":"","children":[{"id":"203","parent":"202","text":"Reactogenicidad frecuente (dolor, fatiga, fiebre) → transitoria 1-3 dias","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"204","parent":"202","text":"No contraindicada en inmunodeprimidos (no viva)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"205","parent":"202","text":"Precaucion: evitar durante inmunosupresion intensa aguda","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"206","parent":"177","text":"Contexto Chile","guid":"","children":[{"id":"207","parent":"206","text":"No incluida en PNI → acceso privado solamente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"208","parent":"206","text":"Costo elevado → barrera real en sistema publico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"209","parent":"206","text":"ADULTO MAYOR con comorbilidad → priorizar recomendacion activa","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"210","parent":"0","text":"Consideraciones en Adulto Mayor","guid":"","children":[{"id":"211","parent":"210","text":"Mayor riesgo de reactivacion por inmunosenescencia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"212","parent":"210","text":"Presentacion atipica: menos vesiculas, mas dolor","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"213","parent":"210","text":"Mayor frecuencia de polineuropatia craneana","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"214","parent":"210","text":"Complicaciones mas frecuentes","guid":"","children":[{"id":"215","parent":"214","text":"Neuralgia posherpetica (dolor cronico)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"216","parent":"214","text":"Paralisis facial permanente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"217","parent":"214","text":"Hipoacusia irreversible","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"218","parent":"210","text":"Interacciones farmacologicas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"219","parent":"218","text":"Aciclovir + AINE → precaucion nefrotoxicidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"220","parent":"218","text":"Corticoides + DM → monitorizar glicemia estrictamente","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"221","parent":"210","text":"STOPP/START: corticoides en DM mal controlada (precausion)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"222","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clinicas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"223","parent":"222","text":"Zoster sine herpete → siempre considerar RHS si paralisis facial + vertigo SIN vesiculas visibles → PCR VZV","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"224","parent":"222","text":"Nistagmo en RHS incluso sin vertigo subjetivo (67%) → evaluar vestibular en TODOS","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"225","parent":"222","text":"Inicio de tratamiento >72h → pronostico significativamente peor → no esperar resultado de examenes para iniciar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"226","parent":"222","text":"Dano vestibular en RHS mas severo y de peor recuperacion que Neuritis Vestibular pura","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"227","parent":"222","text":"Evitar BZD prolongadas → frenan compensacion vestibular central","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"228","parent":"222","text":"Cuidado ocular es EMERGENCIA OFTALMOLOGICA si paralisis facial completa (HB V-VI)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"229","parent":"222","text":"HINTS en RHS: puede haber desviacion oblicua pequena (periferica) → no interpretar como central automaticamente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"230","parent":"222","text":"Rehabilitacion vestibular precoz → fundamental para reducir discapacidad residual","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"231","parent":"222","text":"VER TAMBIEN","guid":"","children":[{"id":"232","parent":"231","text":"→ Neurofisiologia Vestibular (ORL)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"233","parent":"231","text":"→ Schwannoma Vestibular (ORL)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"234","parent":"231","text":"→ AUVP-Neuritis Vestibular (ORL)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"235","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"236","parent":"235","text":"1. Martin-Sanz E, Rueda A, Esteban-Sanchez J, et al. Vestibular Restoration and Adaptation in Vestibular Neuritis and Ramsay Hunt Syndrome With Vertigo. Otol Neurotol. 2017;38(7):e203-e208. DOI: 10.1097/MAO.0000000000001468","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"237","parent":"235","text":"2. Lee J, Choi B, Noh H, et al. Nystagmus in Ramsay Hunt syndrome with or without dizziness. Neurol Sci. 2021;42(1):193-198. DOI: 10.1007/s10072-020-04536-w","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"238","parent":"235","text":"3. Vanstrum EB, Smith E, Weng M, et al. Vestibulopathy in Patients Presenting With Ramsay Hunt Syndrome. Otol Neurotol Open. 2024;4(4):e064. DOI: 10.1097/ONO.0000000000000064","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"239","parent":"235","text":"4. Jahr SH, Wahl MS, Majid B, Samuelsen E. Herpes zoster oticus. Tidsskr Nor Laegeforen. 2021;141. DOI: 10.4045/tidsskr.21.0036","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"240","parent":"235","text":"5. Strupp M, Bisdorff A, Furman J, et al. Acute unilateral vestibulopathy/vestibular neuritis: Diagnostic criteria. J Vestib Res. 2022;32(6):389-406. DOI: 10.3233/VES-220201","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"241","parent":"235","text":"6. Nikkels AF, Schoevaerdts D, et al. Herpes zoster in Belgium: a new solution to an old problem. Acta Clin Belg. 2024;79(3):205-216. DOI: 10.1080/17843286.2024.2350258","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"242","parent":"235","text":"7. Guenther L. Prevention of Shingles in Dermatology Patients on Systemic Medications. Skin Therapy Lett. 2023;28(4):4-6.","guid":"","children"